# Recordings module

Layers: actions · components · errors (`RecordingError extends DomainError`) · hooks
(+`recording-keys.ts`) · **recovery/** (internal submodule, has `index.ts`) · services
(`recording-server.service.ts` server-only; `recording.service.ts` client) · store
(`recording.store.ts` = UI/lifecycle only) · types · utils · validators.

## 🔒 HAPPY FLOW 1 — Manual Recording (behavior MUST NOT change; structure may)
1. Input resi, **validated ≥3 chars** (`no-resi` validator) → 2. Start → `POST /recordings/start`
→ 3. record (MediaRecorder) → 4. duplicate check `GET /recordings/duplicate` → **warning modal on dup**
→ 5. Stop → presign `POST /uploads/presign` → PUT to R2 → save metadata `POST /recordings`
→ 6. library table refreshes.
Duplicate detection is **server-side** (`findRecentDuplicateResi`: exact noResi,
case-insensitive, includes in-progress, 24h window) — keep it there.

## Rules
- Route handlers orchestration only; business logic in services; Prisma via the data layer.
- `recording.store` (Zustand) holds ONLY UI/lifecycle state — never fetched recordings.
  Recordings lists/details come from TanStack Query (`recordingKeys`).
- `recordings/recovery/**` is internal — outside code enters via the recovery module, not deep files.
- Lifecycle/stop-failure classification is pure + tested (`utils/stop-recording-failure.ts`,
  recovery `failure-codes`) — keep the QUOTA_EXCEEDED branch reachable (checked before the broad size match).
- Touching Prisma schema / R2 contract / the flow's behavior → confirm first.
